ing: 1 1/2 cups barbeque sauce (such as Sweet Baby Ray'sÂ®)
3 (1 ounce) packages ranch dressing mix (such as Hidden Valley RanchÂ®)
n: Slow Cooker Honey Barbeque Ranch Wings
des: "Moist and tasty chicken wings that can go with anything. I could see these going well with rice."
ins: Mix barbeque sauce, honey, and ranch dressing together in a large bowl. Dip wings in the sauce until coated. Transfer wings to a 6-quart slow cooker; pour any remaining sauce on top. Cook on High until no longer pink at the bone and the juices run clear, about 4 hours. An instant-read thermometer inserted near the bone should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).
